---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — CalcTax"
  description="How CalcTax.ca handles your data. All tax calculations happen in your browser — your financial data never leaves your device."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <p>
      CalcTax.ca ("the Site") respects your privacy. This policy explains what
      information we collect and how we use it.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Your Calculator Data Stays on Your Device</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>All tax calculations are performed entirely in your web browser.</strong>
      The numbers you enter into our calculators (income, deductions, contributions)
      are not sent to our servers, stored in any database, or shared with any third
      party. Your financial data never leaves your device.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      We currently do not use any third-party analytics services. If we add
      analytics in the future, this policy will be updated before any data
      collection begins.
    </p>

    <h3>Cookies</h3>
    <p>
      The Site itself does not set cookies. However, if you click an affiliate
      link (e.g., to Wealthsimple), the destination site may set cookies on
      your device to track the referral. These cookies are governed by that
      site's own privacy policy, not ours.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can control cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow
      you to refuse cookies or delete existing cookies. Disabling cookies will
      not affect the functionality of our calculators.
    </p>

    <h3>Server Logs</h3>
    <p>
      Our hosting provider (Cloudflare) may automatically collect standard
      server log data including IP addresses, browser type, referring pages,
      and timestamps. This data is used for security, performance monitoring,
      and abuse prevention. We do not access or use this data for marketing
      or user profiling.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
    <p>We do not collect, store, or have access to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your income, tax, or financial information entered into calculators</li>
      <li>Your name, email, or contact information (unless you voluntarily contact us)</li>
      <li>Your Social Insurance Number (SIN) or any government identification</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>
      Any information collected via server logs is used solely for security
      and performance purposes. We do not sell, rent, or share personal
      information with third parties for marketing purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      When you click an affiliate link and leave our Site, the destination
      site's privacy policy applies. Our current affiliate partners are:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Wealthsimple</strong> — <a href="https://www.wealthsimple.com/en-ca/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a></li>
      <li><strong>FreshBooks</strong> — <a href="https://www.freshbooks.com/policies/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Your Rights Under Canadian Privacy Law</h2>
    <p>
      Under the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act
      (PIPEDA) and applicable provincial legislation, you have the right to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Know what personal information we hold about you</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent for data collection</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise these rights, contact us at the address below.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>For visitors from Quebec:</strong> Under Quebec's Act respecting the
      protection of personal information in the private sector (Law 25), you have
      additional rights regarding your personal information, including the right
      to data portability and the right to be informed of automated decision-making.
      Our designated person responsible for the protection of personal information
      can be reached using the contact information below.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Breach Response</h2>
    <p>
      In the unlikely event of a security breach that affects personal information,
      we will notify affected individuals and the Office of the Privacy Commissioner
      of Canada as required by PIPEDA's mandatory breach reporting provisions.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      This Site is not directed at individuals under the age of 18. We do not
      knowingly collect personal information from children.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted
      on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. If we introduce new data
      collection (such as analytics), we will update this policy before collection begins.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your
      privacy rights, contact us at:
    </p>
    <p>
      CalcTax.ca Privacy Inquiries<br />
      Email: privacy@calctax.ca
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
